<!-- Load Splide min css code -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@splidejs/splide@4.1.4/dist/css/splide-core.min.css"/>
<!-- Load Splide min JS code -->
<script defer src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@splidejs/splide@4.1.4/dist/js/splide.min.js"></script>

<!-- Create Splide Element -->
<script defer>
// Pagination Elements used to style in designer must be removed before splide loads to prevent duplicate pagination dots
const removeStylingElements = () => {
    const paginationStyles = document.querySelectorAll(
        ".splide__pagination__page"
    );
    paginationStyles.forEach((dot) => {
        dot.remove();
    });
};

const init = () => {
    removeStylingElements();
    const splide = new Splide("#splide-01", {
    		// EDIT OPTIONS BELOW
        // https://splidejs.com/guides/options/
        type: "slide",
        perMove: 1,
        perPage: 3,
        lazyLoad: false,
        gap: "3rem",
        breakpoints: {
            991: {
                perPage: 2
            },
            767: {
                perPage: 1,
            }
        },
        focus: 0,
        omitEnd: true,
    });

    splide.mount();
};

document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", init);
</script>

<style>
/* You can use the combo classes below to style specific slides or to help with debugging*/
/*
.splide__slide.is-visible {
	padding: 1rem;
  background-color: green;
}
.splide__slide.is-next {
	padding: 1rem;
  background-color: blue;
}
.splide__slide.is-prev {
	padding: 1rem;
  background-color: yellow;
}
.splide__slide.is-active {
	padding: 1rem;
  background-color: red;
}
*/

.splide__arrow:disabled {
	opacity: 0.5;
}
</style>
